                            "text": "When mixing a rock drum kit, phase alignment between the close mics and the {0} is critical. To add punch, the kick drum is often boosted around {1} for 'click' or 'beater' presence. To add weight to the snare without making it muddy, a small boost around {2} is common. To make the entire kit sound cohesive and glued together in the studio space, {3} compression is frequently applied to the drum bus.",
